\": null,\n39\t  \"ac020_passes_5_33x\": false,\n40\t  \"ac020_passes_packet_1_25_margin\": false,\n41\t  \"threadsafe_before_open\": 1,\n42\t  \"threadsafe_after_open\": 1,\n43\t  \"threadsafe_note\": \"sqlite3_threadsafe() is compile-time pinned to 1 by libsqlite3-sys-0.30.1 build.rs:136 (-DSQLITE_THREADSAFE=1). Cannot change at runtime; per SQLite header sqlite3.h:249-252 it returns the compile-time value regardless of sqlite3_config. Not asserted as a B.1 gate per UPDATE 2026-05-03.\",\n44\t  \"sqlite3_config_return_code\": 0,\n45\t  \"sqlite3_shutdown_return_code\": 0,\n46\t  \"sqlite3_initialize_return_code\": 0,\n47\t  \"sqlite3_config_return_code_note\": \"0 = SQLITE_OK. This is the §5 differentiator: the §5 prior revert returned SQLITE_MISUSE = 21 silently because the call was placed inside register_sqlite_vec_extension's Once block after rusqlite had already triggered sqlite3_initialize. B.1 places init_sqlite_runtime at open_locked head BEFORE register_sqlite_vec_extension and BEFORE any Connection::open, so sqlite3_initialize has not yet run and sqlite3_config succeeds. Verified by tests/multithread_wiring.rs assertion sqlite_runtime_config_rc() == Some(0).\",\n48\t  \"init_runs_once_verified\": true,\n49\t  \"decision_rule\": \"KEEP iff concurrent_median_ms <= 80 AND speedup >= 5.0x AND AC-018 green; INCONCLUSIVE in 80-100ms band (recapture + stack B.3); REVERT iff concurrent_median_ms > 115 OR AC-018 red. Per A.4 OVERRIDE update 2026-05-03.\",\n50\t  \"decision_rule_met\": false,\n51\t  \"decision_rule_evaluation\": \"concurrent_median = 120.6 ms > 115 ms threshold (REVERT trigger). Speedup 1.526x is essentially unchanged from A.1 baseline 1.58x (within 1 stddev: stddev_speedup=0.025). Sequential effectively unchanged (+1.1%). Concurrent shifted +4.9% which is ~1.7 stddev — borderline but on the wrong side of the gate. Strict rule: REVERT.\",\n52\t  \"kill_criteria_met\": false,\n53\t  \"kill_criteria_note\": \"Kill rule (B.1 + B.3 stacked < 10% drop ⇒ promote D.1) requires B.3 also to land. B.1 alone shows 0% drop (mild regression within noise). Ready to evaluate after B.3 or in light of C.1 hypothesis below.\",\n54\t  \"reviewer_verdict\": \"PENDING\",\n55\t  \"reviewer_concerns\": [],\n56\t  \"reviewer_log\": \"dev/plan/runs/B1-review-<ts>.md (orchestrator to run)\",\n57\t  \"phase78_review_verdict\": \"PENDING\",\n58\t  \"phase78_review_log\": \"dev/plan/runs/B1-review-phase78-<ts>.md (orchestrator to run)\",\n59\t  \"loc_added\": 119,\n60\t  \"loc_removed\": 0,\n61\t  \"files_changed_pre_revert\": [\n62\t    \"src/rust/crates/fathomdb-engine/src/lib.rs\",\n63\t    \"src/rust/crates/fathomdb-engine/tests/multithread_wiring.rs\"\n64\t  ],\n65\t  \"files_changed\": [],\n66\t  \"commit_sha\": \"none\",\n67\t  \"git_status_clean_after_revert\": true,\n68\t  \"data_for_pivot\": \"APPLIED-BUT-DIDN'T-HELP. sqlite3_config(SQLITE_CONFIG_MULTITHREAD) was correctly invoked at open_locked head BEFORE any Connection::open; rc=SQLITE_OK=0 (vs §5's silent 21). init_sqlite_runtime is OnceLock-cached (idempotent across reopens). Yet the AC-020 ratio is unchanged (1.526x vs A.1 1.58x; concurrent 120.6 vs 115 ms — within noise). Interpretation: runtime threading-mode downgrade from SERIALIZED (compile-pinned 1) to MULTITHREAD does NOT relieve the bottleneck. Two explanations consistent with the A.1 hot-symbol set (__aarch64_swp4_rel/_cas4_acq dominant in concurrent): (a) per-connection mutex elimination requires compile-time SQLITE_THREADSAFE=2 + SQLITE_NO_MUTEX, not runtime config — promotes C.1 to next; (b) the contended primitive is the WAL-pager spinlock which is unaffected by threading-mode flag — promotes D.1 (per-conn lookaside or different reader architecture). Recommend running C.1 first (cheaper to test the hypothesis: rebuild libsqlite3-sys with -DSQLITE_THREADSAFE=2 and re-measure). If C.1 still shows no improvement, kill the mutex track and pivot to D.1.\",\n69\t  \"unexpected_observations\": \"The 5 runs were tightly clustered (concurrent stddev 2.98 ms) with no outliers; AC-018 stayed green; AC-017 stayed green. The B.1 intervention is provably wired (config_rc=0 cached in OnceLock, idempotent across reopens), eliminating the §5-class silent-no-op failure mode. The fact that wiring works but perf is flat is itself a high-confidence signal that the runtime threading-mode flag is NOT the right knob — the dominant SQLite primitives we observed in A.1 (__aarch64_swp4_rel, __aarch64_cas4_acq, ___pthread_mutex_lock) are not the SQLite global-mutex which CONFIG_MULTITHREAD relaxes; they are likely WAL-pager spinlocks and per-connection mutexes that only SQLITE_THREADSAFE=2 (compile-time, C.1 territory) can disable. Pre-existing compile errors in tests/{compatibility,cursors,lifecycle_observability}.rs are A.0 baseline (noted in A.1 pre_flight_notes); not B.1's regression.\",\n70\t  \"next_phase_recommendation\": \"C1\",\n71\t  \"next_phase_recommendation_rationale\": \"B.1 ruled out the runtime threading-mode hypothesis with a clean, observable gate (config_rc=0 yet ratio flat). Two surviving hypotheses: C.1 (compile-time SQLITE_THREADSAFE=2 / SQLITE_NO_MUTEX rebuild — directly addresses the per-connection mutex symbols dominating the concurrent flame) and D.1 (architectural — per-conn lookaside or alt reader topology). C.1 is a smaller-radius intervention and tests a more specific hypothesis with the same evidence stack; recommend C.1 first. If C.1 also lands flat, kill the mutex track per the A.4 kill criterion and promote D.1.\",\n72\t  \"tests_run_summary\": {\n73\t    \"lib_tests\": \"1 passed\",\n74\t    \"multithread_wiring\": \"2 passed (init_sqlite_runtime_runs_on_engine_open_and_captures_sqlite_ok, init_sqlite_runtime_is_idempotent_across_engine_reopens)\",\n75\t    \"perf_gates\": \"AC-017 green, AC-018 green, AC-020 long-run failed (expected — perf gate not met)\",\n76\t    \"lifecycle_reliability\": \"4 passed, 3 ignored (AC-021/022a green)\",\n77\t    \"vector_contracts\": \"7 passed\",\n78\t    \"projection_runtime\": \"12 passed, 1 ignored\",\n79\t    \"op_store\": \"7 passed\",\n80\t    \"error_taxonomy\": \"12 passed\",\n81\t    \"instrumentation_methods\": \"5 passed\",\n82\t    \"cursor_read_after_write\": \"1 passed\",\n83\t    \"search_result_shape\": \"2 passed\",\n84\t    \"property_template\": \"1 passed\",\n85\t    \"compile_errors_pre_existing\": [\"tests/compatibility.rs\", \"tests/cursors.rs\", \"tests/lifecycle_observability.rs (test file with compile errors at lines 414/446/453/489)\"],\n86\t    \"compile_errors_pre_existing_note\": \"A.0/A.1 baseline; documented in dev/plan/runs/A1-perf-capture-output.json pre_flight_notes.build_note. Not introduced by B.1.\"\n87\t  }\n88\t}\n89\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"8996a1e6-f0cf-41f6-bd76-ad56a5a9b42e","uuid":"d0d185a4-cc5f-462a-ab43-d148c4bd8238","timestamp":"2026-05-04T02:27:58.033Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/tmp/fdb-pack5-C1-threadsafe2-rebuild-20260504T022727Z/dev/plan/runs/B1-multithread-wiring-output.json","content":"{\n  \"phase\": \"B1\",\n  \"decision\": \"REVERT\",\n  \"before\": {\n    \"sequential_ms\": 182,\n    \"concurrent_ms\": 115,\n    \"bound_ms\": null,\n    \"speedup\": 1.58,\n    \"n\": 5,\n    \"raw_runs\": [\n      {\"sequential_ms\": 189, \"concurrent_ms\": 120},\n      {\"sequential_ms\": 199, \"concurrent_ms\": 110},\n      {\"sequential_ms\": 182, \"concurrent_ms\": 117},\n      {\"sequential_ms\": 179, \"concurrent_ms\": 115},\n      {\"sequential_ms\": 176, \"concurrent_ms\": 112}\n    ],\n    \"source\": \"A.1 baseline (dev/plan/runs/A1-perf-capture-output.json, commit fec71a0)\"\n  },\n  \"after\": {\n    \"raw_runs\": [\n      {\"sequential_ms\": 181.5, \"concurrent_ms\": 121.6, \"bound_ms\": 34.0, \"speedup\": 1.493},\n      {\"sequential_ms\": 178.1, \"concurrent_ms\": 115.1, \"bound_ms\": 33.4, \"speedup\": 1.547},\n      {\"sequential_ms\": 189.0, \"concurrent_ms\": 124.0, \"bound_ms\": 