Cargo.toml\",\n    \"src/rust/crates/fathomdb-engine/tests/compile_options.rs\"\n  ],\n  \"files_changed\": [\n    \"dev/plan/runs/C1-evidence-compile-options.txt\",\n    \"dev/plan/runs/C1-threadsafe2-rebuild-output.json\"\n  ],\n  \"commit_sha\": \"none\",\n  \"data_for_pivot\": \"THREADSAFE=2 rebuild applied correctly and verified (sqlite3_threadsafe()==2, PRAGMA THREADSAFE=2, two independent green tests before revert). AC-020 concurrent median 121.5ms vs A.1 115ms (+5.65%) — essentially flat, speedup 1.509x vs 1.58x (-4.48%). Kill criterion MET: C.1 was the strongest compile-time mutex intervention (replaces B.1+B.3 stacked per update log); result is within ±5% of baseline (barely outside at +5.65%, within 1.2 stddev). The A.2 hot symbols (__aarch64_swp4_rel, __aarch64_cas4_acq, ___pthread_mutex_lock) are NOT SQLite compile-time threading mutexes — they are unaffected by SQLITE_THREADSAFE=2. Promote D.1 (per-connection lookaside or alt reader architecture). Reverting C.1 cleanly restores A.1 baseline state; Cargo.lock unchanged.\",\n  \"unexpected_observations\": \"sqlite3_threadsafe() confirmed returning compile-time value (2 after rebuild, as A.3 predicted). The THREADSAFE=2 compile flag was applied unambiguously via -USQLITE_THREADSAFE -DSQLITE_THREADSAFE=2 (undefine-before-redefine pattern matching libsqlite3-sys bundled-nosafety idiom). No new c_char/i8/u8 FFI hardcodes introduced. Pre-existing compile errors in tests/compatibility.rs, tests/cursors.rs, tests/lifecycle_observability.rs (A.0 baseline) unchanged. MUTEX_PTHREADS still appears in compile_options with THREADSAFE=2 — this is expected; MUTEX_PTHREADS is the mutex implementation backend, not the threading mode. The per-connection mutex is still physically present in the binary at THREADSAFE=2 (it is only disabled at THREADSAFE=0 or with SQLITE_NO_MUTEX). This may partially explain why the perf is flat: THREADSAFE=2 removes only the global allocator/pcache serialization mutex, not the per-connection mutex which dominates in the ReaderPool read path.\",\n  \"next_phase_recommendation\": \"D1\",\n  \"kill_criterion_status\": \"MET: C.1 concurrent median 121.5ms vs A.1 115ms (+5.65% ≈ flat within noise); speedup 1.509x vs 1.58x (-4.48%). Both THREADSAFE=2 (runtime path, B.1) and THREADSAFE=2 (compile-time path, C.1) show no improvement. Per A.4 kill criterion: mutex track is wrong — promote D.1 (per-conn lookaside, alt reader architecture, or WAL-pager contention investigation).\"\n}\n","structuredPatch":[],"originalFile":null,"userModified":false}}
